1. Two Environmental management and protection policies, 1 bill and 4 Acts of same are under review. The Two Policies include; The National Env. Policy, The Climate Change policy & the bill include the National Protected Area Authority & conservation Trust Fund bill. The 4 Acts includes, the Forestry Act 1998, Wildlife Conservation Act 1972, EPA Act 2008/2010, & the Climate change Act. The Ministry of Environment has produced the first draft of Five of the revised policies and bills;

2. Four MDAs (Ministry of Environment, The Environment Protection Agency, The National Protected Area Authority and the National Water Resources Mgt. Agency) were capacitated by reviewing 3 Environmental management and protection policies and 4 Acts of same;

3. Support to the National Water Resources Management Agency (NWRMA) saw the development of three regulations, namely: Water use, groundwater development and protection and dam safety regulations. Draft of these documents done, awaiting validation;

4. One communications Strategy for the National Water Resource Management Agency was developed drafted, validated and finalized; 

5. Ten (10) Hectares of reclaimed mine out land was cultivated with rice which had good harvest;

6. 50 artisanal miners were capacitated in improved farming techniques which enabled them to cultivate 10 Hectares of land for Agricultural productivity;

7. Ward Disaster Management committees were not established due to Covid 19 public emergencies;

8. One Disaster Risks Reduction and Management hand book for schools were developed and validated by school stakeholders;

9. DRR Policy has been developed but not yet finalised, awaiting the incorperation of the Sendia framework and the National Disaster Management Agency organogram by the World bank that has contracted a consultant to do the final review,

10. UNDP capacitated 2 MDAs (Meteorological Agency and Office Of National Security) to disseminate Early warning information in coastal communities;

11. The Nationally Appropriate Mitigation Action (NAMA) framework was reviewed to identify weaknesses and have it updated to enable it to attract funding for carbon financing;
12. No proposal for carbon financing was developed

